article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 71, Louisiana-Monroe 68
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander and Matt Kingsley scored 18 points each and Nick Shaw had a double-double to help lead Stephen F. Austin to a 71-68 victory over Louisiana-Monroe on Wednesday night. Shaw had 16 points and 16 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (3-1). Eric Bell scored 12 points and had nine assists for Stephen F. Austin. Stephen F. Austin led by as much as 14 points in the second half after holding a narrow 38-34 halftime lead. Louisiana-Monroe cut the lead to the final margin of 71-68 with 45 seconds left. Tony Hooper led the Warhawks (1-3) with 23 points. Jordan Payne added 15. The Lumberjacks shot 45 percent for the game to the Warhawks' 39 percent.
